<br>
What I do...<br>
<br>
Summon a top level air pet...this is the best pet for this guy, he is a caster and the stuns make a big difference.<br>
<br>
Equip your pet with 2 lev rings, 2 coldstones and shard of the core and 2 daggers of summoning...this gives the air pet very nice defense against O.<br>
<br>
Make sure you have a full clip of bandages in case one of O's nasty dots get through, it does occasionaly happen.<br>
<br>
Forget malise, I was working with an enchanter who was tashing and I would malise and the sucker resisted my rains all the time...this is really a waste of mana.  he has some serious resists so why bother?<br>
<br>
What does help?  Nullify magic!  Pull with this spell!  I can't emphasise this enough...it drops his SoW and his other buffs.  This makes a huge difference....<br>
<br>
I then follow with a rain, which is usually resisted somewhat, however I noticed once I turned 40 I get less total resists and more partial resists...<br>
<br>
I then follow up with blaze once or twice depending upon how well the pet is doing and finish with a shock of sword or other quick casting dd once he stsrts to run....(I am not a big fan of bolts and with this guy and his hitpoints I would rather be sure with a lesser dmg dd than miss with a bigger damage bolt.)<br>
<br>
Good luck.... <p>Everwind Gale

